  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empowered Parents, Inclusive Communities for Deaf</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Project will train and provide start up loans to 180 mothers of deaf children who are unemployed in rural Uganda. The small businesses include: goat rearing, vegetable growing, chicken rearing, mushroom growing, tailoring and small scale shop. The training will include: Business skills, Planning, Market Research, and value added production. By learning a marketable skill the mothers will generate income and lift themselves out of poverty to sustain their deaf children in education</narrative>
  </description>
